    "12 Notwithstanding this balanced list of instructors, the instruction itself was more emphatically delivered by the conservative instructors.",
    "As George Priest, a regularly participating instructor, observed: [Manne] did not provide for too much balance... [the liberal economists] were cabined by topics far from familiar to them.",
